The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, July 07, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Monday, July 7, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Lower Circular Road, between Camac Street and Lansdowne Road, due to work on the AJC Bose Road flyover. Buses and minibuses heading towards Alipore zoo will take the Lansdowne Road-Elgin Road-Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Chowringhee-Queensway-Hospital Road-Lower Circular Road route. Those travelling towards Beckbagan will take the Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Hazra Road-Ballygunge Phari-Syed Amir Ali Avenue route.				 																On stage				 																																	A theatre production, directed by Jayant Kripalani, to be staged at GD Birla Sabhagar at 7 pm. Hidden Fires, a collection of monologues by Manjula Padmanabhan, will be released on the occasion.				 																Film				 																																	Way Back Home, a film by Supriyo Sen, will be screened at the British Council at 6 pm. Mrinal Sen will attend.				 																Orissa fest				 																																	Sambalpuri, ghumura and gotipua dances will be performed in the Orissa Festival at Swabhumi, 5 pm to 9.30 pm.
